    <div id="post-1732" class="post-1732 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized tag-big-data tag-digital-culture tag-digital-unconscious tag-education tag-intelligence tag-networks tag-old-media tag-smart-revolution tag-transparency"> 
     <div class="post-entry"> 
      <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/coping-with-the-digital-unconscious/" title="Coping with the digital unconscious"> <img width="150" height="150" src="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/wp-content/uploads/DdKerckhove_post.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="DdKerckhove_post"> </a> 
      <h1 class="post-title"><a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/coping-with-the-digital-unconscious/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Coping with the digital unconscious">Coping with the digital unconscious<br><br></a></h1> 
      <!-- .post-meta --> 
      <div class="post-meta"> 
       <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author posted">Posted on </span>
       <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/coping-with-the-digital-unconscious/" title="12:04 pm" rel="bookmark"><span class="timestamp">18/12/2014</span></a>
       <span class="byline"> by </span>
       <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/author/uoc/" title="View all posts by UOC">UOC</a></span> 
       <span class="comments-link"> <span class="mdash">—</span> <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/coping-with-the-digital-unconscious/#respond" title="Comment on Coping with the digital unconscious">No Comments ↓</a> </span> 
      </div>
      <!-- end of .post-meta --> 
      <p><strong>By <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/open-thinkers/#DdKerckhove">Derrick de Kerckhove</a>, professor, Università degli Studi di Napoli Federico II, and IN3 visiting professor</strong></p> 
      <p>With the smart revolution, tech companies and services are getting lots of data coming from our behaviour and use of connected devices. According to Derrick de Kerckhove, there is a challenge we might face regarding this issue: are we ready to cope with what he calls our “digital unconscious”? Information about ourselves that we can’t even imagine it exists is being stored and used for profit. How can we protect ourselves as we become more and more transparent? Don’t miss De Kerckhove’s ideas in the short video below. </p>
      <div class="read-more">
       <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/coping-with-the-digital-unconscious/">Read more ›</a>
      </div> 
      <p>
       <!-- end of .read-more --></p> 
     </div>
     <!-- end of .post-entry --> 
