    <div id="post-1723" class="post-1723 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized tag-ar tag-art tag-augmented-reality tag-consciousness tag-elder tag-mixed-reality tag-vr tag-wisdom-technologies"> 
     <div class="post-entry"> 
      <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/wisdom-technologies-and-human-consciousness/" title="Wisdom technologies and human consciousness"> <img width="150" height="150" src="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/wp-content/uploads/SRyu_post.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="SRyu_post"> </a> 
      <h1 class="post-title"><a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/wisdom-technologies-and-human-consciousness/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Wisdom technologies and human consciousness">Wisdom technologies and human consciousness<br><br></a></h1> 
      <!-- .post-meta --> 
      <div class="post-meta"> 
       <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author posted">Posted on </span>
       <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/wisdom-technologies-and-human-consciousness/" title="11:44 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="timestamp">04/12/2014</span></a>
       <span class="byline"> by </span>
       <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/author/uoc/" title="View all posts by UOC">UOC</a></span> 
       <span class="comments-link"> <span class="mdash">—</span> <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/wisdom-technologies-and-human-consciousness/#respond" title="Comment on Wisdom technologies and human consciousness">No Comments ↓</a> </span> 
      </div>
      <!-- end of .post-meta --> 
      <p><strong>By <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/open-thinkers/#SRyu">Semi Ryu</a>, associate professor, School of the Arts, Virginia Commonwealth University</strong></p> 
      <p>What can artistic performance tell us about new technologies? If art is about arising feelings and sensations, what insights can we get from the intersection of both worlds? According to Semi Ryu’s experience, mixed reality technologies — like augmented reality — can stir things up in our mind, depending on who is using it and whether it supports similar nature of human experience. Check Ryu’s reflections about “wisdom technologies” in the short video below. </p>
      <div class="read-more">
       <a href="http://openthoughtsmarter.blogs.uoc.edu/wisdom-technologies-and-human-consciousness/">Read more ›</a>
      </div> 
      <p>
       <!-- end of .read-more --></p> 
     </div>
     <!-- end of .post-entry --> 
